    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is an MRI of the coccyx painful?",
        "answer": " The **MRI Coccyx** scan itself is painless. You will not feel magnetic fields or radio waves. Some individuals may find it uncomfortable to lie still. Contrast injection is mild.  "
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does an MRI Coccyx take?",
        "answer": "Typically, the procedure takes 30-60 minutes. Duration varies depending on sequences and contrast.  "
      },
      {
        "question": "Is sedation available for claustrophobic patients?",
        "answer": "Yes, light oral sedation is provided under medical supervision.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home after the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you received sedation. In that case, bring an escort.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will the report be ready?",
        "answer": "Most reports are ready the same evening; urgent cases within 2 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need a referral?",
        "answer": "A doctor’s prescription is mandatory as per regulations.\n"
      }
    ],
